cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SI

This paper deals with language games and communication between two players, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a model that captures human behavior, which involves reasoning and decision-making, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also discusses the importance of pragmatic reasoning, which could place it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
